{
  "claim_boundary": "cuNxon GPU execution has runtime/dynamics viability and exposes snapshot/pattern/multi-sphere/interface APIs from Python, but task-coupled probes remain diagnostic/negative: pattern recall readouts are flat zero, the multi-sphere action adapter decodes all cases to query, a 108-sample long sweep matches constant-action baselines at 0.333333 accuracy, the supervised motor-target adapter stays at constant-query baseline accuracy, and the resident action probe also stays at baseline accuracy across every epoch. The interface semantics probe supports absolute neuron-index readout mapping, while the source semantics audit found no desired-output API surface and explains why teacher-forcing absolute output-neuron target ports through sensory inputs is unsupported by the kernel path. The input-proxy target probe confirms expected targets can be observed on supported input-class proxy ports during training, but evaluation motor readout still remains flat query/baseline-level. The external-drive port-window probe confirms the sharper boundary: identical external values drive input-class windows in infer/train, while hidden/output windows stay zero in this controlled 4/4/4 setup, so those windows should not be treated as desired-output channels. The completed four-hour VRAM-resident run adds process-residence/state-file evidence and flat infer-only dynamics evidence only. The task-coupled resident action probe adds explicit scoring but still does not beat trivial baselines. The new Aigarth readout semantics probe shows a different lower-level surface: relative demo readout margin improved 1.000000->1.500000, while absolute output readout margin improved 0.625000->1.500000 on the same two-pattern fitness task. This is positive interface/evolution evidence, but not holdout/action evidence and not a Neuraxon-Hybrid decision-quality win. The Aigarth holdout/action probe is the first cuNxon action lane in this stack to beat constant-action baselines on a tiny balanced train/holdout set (0.666667 holdout/overall), but it remains toy Aigarth/evolution evidence rather than broad learning, intelligence, or production-readiness evidence.",
